#1 <s>As an introverted creative working independently and placing great value on privacy, it shouldn't be a contradiction, but it often is. Most online sources and coaches advise working with (evil) tech giants and being extroverted. Advertise here, follow the algorithm, show your personality. Get a blue tick for that service, be available around the clock, answer inquiries with a video of yourself, respond immediately. Video, video, video.
#2 <s>1/3
#3 <s>For me, this is a year of changes.
#4 <s>I don't want to feed the tech giants with money, data, and my energy. Nor do I want to follow coaches who have their own extroverted solution and try to sell it to everyone. I am looking for new ways to run my business and am simultaneously fighting against my long-held belief that one must do things in a specific way to succeed.
#5 <s>Wünscht mir Glück!
I have already taken the first steps.
I terminated my Facebook account, removed all Meta and Pinterest trackers from my website, and deleted my private WhatsApp account.
Yesterday, I also removed Google Analytics, the last external tracker from my website, and feel good about it.
Lately, I subscribed to a European CRM to have better DSGVO support, and will be moving my business there in the upcoming weeks.
I transferred my MX account to Proton and now have full SPF, DKIM, and DMARC without having to pay anything to Google for normal email validation.
3/3
