@user4 @user3 You can do it! And I am happy to help you with my experiences.
Website: Check out @user5. It seems simple, looks good, and is open-source. I will switch one of my websites to this before the next renewal.
Signal: Check out cal.com. It is an open-source calendar service with integrations that allow planning of video calls with Element Call, Jitsi, etc. Signal is also supported, but I have not yet tested whether it works for messages or video calls.
I can recommend @user6. E2EE, decentralized, open-source.
